{
  "id": "019ce9a4-9cfa-71c2-b7d6-26c81fa1b0c3",
  "content": "## Dashboard Completion Design Decisions (Features 7, 9, 10) — 2026-03-13\n\nDesign spec: `docs/rfcs/2026-03-13-dashboard-completion-design.md`\n\n### D1: OTEL Trace Context via Custom tracing Layer\nA custom `OtelContextLayer` in `corvia-telemetry` bridges OpenTelemetry span context into JSON log output. The layer reads `OtelData` from span extensions (populated by tracing-opentelemetry) and injects `otel.trace_id`, `otel.span_id`, `otel.parent_span_id` into fmt JSON output. Conditional — no-op when OTEL is not configured. Requires significant refactor of `init_telemetry()` layer composition order. Separate from RAG pipeline's business-logic `trace_id: Uuid::now_v7()`.\n\n### D2: Enhanced GcReport\n`GcReport` expanded from 1 field (`orphans_rolled_back`) to 7 fields: `duration_ms`, `stale_transitioned`, `closed_sessions_cleaned`, `agents_suspended`, `entries_deduplicated`, `started_at`. In-memory `GcHistory` (VecDeque, max 50) stored on `AppState` in `rest.rs`.\n\n### D3: GC is Manual-Only\nNo periodic GC timer exists. Dashboard GC endpoint returns `scheduled: false`. GcPanel shows \"Manual trigger only\" with a \"Run GC Now\" button. Future: if periodic timer added, field becomes `true` with `next_scheduled_secs`.\n\n### D4: Live Sessions via Polling\n`GET /api/dashboard/sessions/live` polls `SessionManager::list_open()` + staging dir reads. No WebSocket — consistent with existing dashboard poll architecture (usePoll, 5s interval). Frontend `LiveSessionsBar` component shows active session pills at top of Agents tab.\n\n### D5: Span Drill-Down with Waterfall\nTrace tree reconstruction from log lines grouped by `trace_id`, sorted by timestamp, built into parent-child trees via `parent_span_id`. `SpanNode` struct with `start_offset_ms` (delta from root span timestamp). Waterfall UI with nested horizontal bars, color-coded by module. Graceful degradation: \"Enable OTEL exporter\" message when no trace context available.\n\n### D6: SpanStats Percentiles\n`SpanStats` gains `p50_ms`, `p95_ms`, `p99_ms` from rolling window of last 1000 durations per span name. Capped at 50 tracked span names. Percentiles work regardless of OTEL — only need `elapsed_ms`.\n\n### D7: ParsedTrace Fields are Optional\nNew `trace_id`, `span_id`, `parent_span_id` fields on `ParsedTrace::Span` are `Option<String>` for backward compatibility with log lines predating OtelContextLayer.\n\n### D8: Build Order\nShared infrastructure first (OtelContextLayer + enhanced GcReport), then Live Sessions, GC Dashboard, Span Drill-Down.\n\n### New Endpoints (4 total)\n- `GET /api/dashboard/gc` — GC history + last run + scheduled status\n- `POST /api/dashboard/gc/run` — trigger GC, return full GcReport\n- `GET /api/dashboard/sessions/live` — active sessions with staging state\n- `GET /api/dashboard/traces/recent?limit=N` — recent traces as parent-child trees\n\n### New Files (4 total)\n- `crates/corvia-telemetry/src/otel_context_layer.rs` — custom Layer bridging OTEL→fmt\n- `tools/corvia-dashboard/src/components/GcPanel.tsx` — GC operations panel\n- `tools/corvia-dashboard/src/components/WaterfallView.tsx` — span drill-down waterfall\n- `tools/corvia-dashboard/src/components/LiveSessionsBar.tsx` — active session pills bar",
